      "step_index": 3,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "**Structural alerts for CYP2D6 inhibition**\n- Classic CYP2D6 inhibitors often contain a **protonatable tertiary amine** (cationic at physiological pH) plus **one or more aromatic rings** (quinidine-/fluoxetine-/paroxetine-like).  \n- This molecule has the aromatic bulk, but **lacks the key cationic center**.",
